No. 8. An act relating to expanding the scope of hate-motivated crimes.
(H.118)
It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
Sec. 1. 13 V.S.A. § 1455 is amended to read:
§ 1455. HATE-MOTIVATED CRIMES
(a) A person who commits, causes to be committed, or attempts to commit
any crime and whose conduct is motivated, in whole or in part, by the victim’s
another person’s or a group of persons’ actual or perceived membership in a
protected category shall be subject to the following penalties:
(1) If the maximum penalty for the underlying crime is one year or less,
the penalty for a violation of this section shall be imprisonment for not more
than two years or a fine of not more than $2,000.00, or both.
(2) If the maximum penalty for the underlying crime is more than one
year but less than five years, the penalty for a violation of this section shall be
imprisonment for not more than five years or a fine of not more than
$10,000.00, or both.
(3) If the maximum penalty for the underlying crime is five years or
more, the penalty for the underlying crime shall apply; however, the court shall
consider the motivation of the defendant as a factor in sentencing.
(b) The victim’s A person’s or a group of persons’ actual or perceived
membership in a protected category or categories need not be the predominant
reason or the sole reason for the defendant’s conduct.
